'''Adrián Andrés Cubas''' (born 11 May 1996) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as [[midfielder]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]. Born in Argentina, he plays for the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

==Club career==
Cubas joined French club [[Nîmes Olympique|Nîmes]] from Argentine side [[Talleres de Córdoba|Talleres]] in 2020.<ref name="delprat">{{cite news |last1=Delprat |first1=Colin |title=Nîmes Olympique. Vers un départ d'Andrés Cubas en ligue américaine |trans-title=Nîmes Olympique. Andrés Cubas set to leave for the American league |url=https://www.lagazettedenimes.fr/sport/2022-04-13-nimes-olympique-vers-un-depart-d-andres-cubas-en-ligue-americaine/ |access-date=23 November 2025 |work=La Gazette de Nîmes |date=13 April 2022 |language=French}}</ref> The transfer fee paid to Talleres was reported as around €3 million.<ref name="delprat"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Andrés Cubas quitte le Nîmes Olympique pour les Whitecaps de Vancouver |trans-title=Andrés Cubas leaves Nîmes Olympique for the Vancouver Whitecaps |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/andres-cubas-quitte-le-nimes-olympique-pour-les-whitecaps-de-vancouver |access-date=23 November 2025 |work={{ill|So Foot|fr}} |date=29 April 2022 |language=French}}</ref>

On 28 April 2022, he signed a contract with [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] until June 2026.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=Vancouver Whitecaps|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/vwfc-acquire-cubas|title=Whitecaps FC acquire Paraguayan international midfielder Andrés Cubas from Nîmes Olympique|date=28 April 2022|access-date=29 April 2022}}</ref> He was purchased for a reported fee of $3 million from Nîmes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le Nîmes Olympique serait endetté à hauteur de 30 millions d'euros |trans-title=Nîmes Olympique is reportedly €30 million in debt |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/le-nimes-olympique-serait-endette-a-hauteur-de-30-millions-deuros-france |access-date=23 November 2025 |work=So Foot |date=28 April 2022 |language=French}}</ref>

On February 24, 2026, he signed a contract extension with the Whitecaps through the 2027/28 season.<ref>https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/vwfc-cubas-contract-extension</ref>

== Personal life ==
Cubas's father is from Paraguay.<ref>[http://www.minutouno.com/notas/346313-ramon-diaz-quiere-nacionalizar-paraguayo-una-las-joyitas-boca Ramón Díaz quiere nacionalizar paraguayo a una de las joyitas de Boca] {{in lang|es}}</ref>

